    "csaf_version": "2.0",
    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for transfig.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The transfig utility creates a makefile which translates FIG (created by xfig) or PIC figures into a specified LaTeX graphics language (for example, PostScript(TM)).  Transfig is used to create TeX documents which are portable (i.e., they can be printed in a wide variety of environments).  Install transfig if you need a utility for translating FIG or PIC figures into certain graphics languages.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* xfig: xfig: Stack-overflow allows possible code execution via local input manipulation (CVE-2025-46397)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
